          {
            "commit": "878f9b75b7bc9deb5f74a510951c4874c0b6e58f",
            "subject": "LU-56 lnet: Partitioned LNet networks"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-06-15 15:56:44.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-06-15 15:56:44.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-56 lnet: allow user to bind NI on CPTs",
        "message": "LU-56 lnet: allow user to bind NI on CPTs\n\nBy default, NI will be bond on all CPTs, which means messages for a\nNI could be handled by LND threads on any CPT (hashed by NID).\nThis patch add a new parameter for NI configuration, it allows user\nto bind NI on specified CPT(s):\n\n- tcp0(eth1)[0,1]\n  bind NI (tcp0) on CPT0 and CPT1\n- o2ib(ib0)[2-5]\n  bind NI (o2ib) on CPT2,3,4,5\n\nExpression between square brackets are CPTs that user wants this NI\nto bind, if user provided this expression, messages for the NI\nwill only be handled by LND threads running on specified CPTs.\n\nThis is an intermediate patch, to get this feature we also need\nupcoming LND patches.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I706a92c6da181ed0fec857cc25b5ae27a7a7c36b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
